BEGIN_PGML

[@ image("UBC-FLU-18-060.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

As shown in the diagram, water flows through an elbow assembly. The water enters the assembly at [`V_1 = [$V1]`] [`m/s`] and [`P_1=[$P1]`] [`kPa`] through the inlet which has an area [`A_1=2600`] [`mm^2`]. The outlet has an area [`A_2=650`] [`mm^2`] and is open to the atmosphere. What is the required force to hold the elbow? Use a water density of [`\rho_{H_2O}=999`] [`kg/m^3`].

[`R_x=`] [____]{"$Ans"} [`N`]

END_PGML

